		{"id":"c1ebc23336d3dd85","type":"text","text":"[[GEMINI_CHAT_LOG_EXTRACTED]]\n\nThere is a famous theorem in topology regarding the **Heawood Conjecture**.\n\n- On a Sphere (or Plane), you need **4 colors** to color any map so no two touching regions have the same color.\n    \n- On a Klein Bottle, you need **6 colors** to do the same.","x":5646,"y":-709,"width":520,"height":220},
